[div class=p 
	[em 
		" The Battle of Olympus
	]em
	" (オリュンポスの戦い) is set in ancient Greece. A mortal man named Orpheus receives help from the gods and nymphs in his quest to save his lover Helene from Hades. People often compare this game with 
	[em 
		[a class=intlink href=/Game/Nes-zelda-ii-the-adventure-of-link 
			"Zelda 2
		]a
	]em
	" because of its similar gameplay.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This movie is 9:11 faster than 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Arc 
		"Arc
	]a
	"'s 
	[a class=intlink href=/292M 
		"version
	]a
	", mostly because of the utilization of a gameplay-altering glitch: pressing Left+Right simultaneously in order to make Orpheus move with almost unlimited velocity growth. The trick is documented at 
	(__wikiLink|/GameResources/NES/BattleOfOlympus|GameResources/NES/BattleOfOlympus)
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The route used in this movie is decided by a few things the hero (Orpheus) must do:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Collect three fragments of love in order to activate the Tartarus entry.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Get a key to access the second fragment's location.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Get the Eyeball of Graeae to see invisible doors (to access the first fragment's location).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Get a sword in Peloponnesus. It is needed to kill the three-headed guardian with respawning heads (Cerberus) in Tartarus.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Collect 60 olives in order to buy the ocarina, which will be needed to cross the sea to get to Crete and Tartarus.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Get a harp in order to call Pegasus. It makes the route faster.
	]li
]ul
